			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I went with a cleric and haven't looked back.  I considered druid, shaman & beastlord but decided that i want to <span style="font-style: italic">play my mage</span> and box the other i.e. I do not want to be forced to play the box any more than I absolutely have to.  With the best hp/ac buffs in the game, lowest cost & best CH - the cleric's keyboard gets used extremely little.  And believe me rez is uber handy - I'll take that over snare or slow any day.  You get an almost total disregard for your life and are willing to try crazy stuff because the risk simply goes away.
<br />

<br />
I would expect a druid or shaman would be better choices in different situations if you were willing to actively play them while your mage sits idle.  
<br />

<br />
I play my mage.  The cleric is just my pet's bitch.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=501504">Anthe Battlecaster</a>
<br />
Uses
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=962390">Improved Healing V</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
