			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I triple account on 1 box (it really doesn't take much, 1.4 Athalon,768MB Ram, 64Meg GEForce II). I don't use a programmable  keyboard or anything.
<br />

<br />
I went Mage as primary with Enchanter and cleric in support.  The key is making good macros for the bots.  I lean heavily on the /stand; /target; /cast;/ sit macro a ton.
<br />

<br />
Edit oh and as to why each class:
<br />
Chanter:  Crack, Slow, Haste and DC for another pet/DPS
<br />
Cleric:  Buffs, big heals and the inevitable rezz
<br />

<br />
Currently I'm levelling them up to play with my mage using an SK as a tank.  Can't wait to have a fully buffed pet tanking!
<br />

<br />
Decided against:
<br />
Druid: Snare, SoW and Dots would be nice but went more for complete independence.  Dont want to rely on running back to town for KEI.  Run speed removes the need for SoW and mage will nuke down runners (or I just use earth pet).
<br />

<br />
Shaman:  Tough choice here, great class.  Buffs are nice, good heals, dots and a pet.  Just decided on going for easy to play classes to minimize my workload.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
