			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">So far I have done it with a Cleric and a Shaman.
<br />

<br />
Cheals are nice, but Shammy Slow has given better results for me.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Cleric</span>
<br />
HPS: 1405 - Virt
<br />
AC: 72 - Virt
<br />

<br />
Spell Pros
<br />
- Pacification:  Have a guild cleric that pull Ikk trials using this to get solos.
<br />
- Blessing of Reverence - 10% spell haste may come in very handy. Stacks with gear
<br />
- Bulwark of Vie - Damage Mitigation
<br />
Best healing spells in the game to allow efficient mana use and speed healing when necessary.
<br />
- Yalp Line - Decent Mana regen addition.
<br />

<br />
Spell Cons.
<br />
- Without some form of slow, you can chew up Mana pretty fast.  
<br />

<br />
Other Notes:
<br />
- This combo rocked pre mod rod nerf since you basically could go from OOM to FM wiht a few rods and cheals <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="wink" border="0" />
<br />
- Always nice to have a pocket rezzer for those occasional mistakes <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="wink" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Shaman</span>
<br />
HPS: 544 Focus of Soul (plus STR/DEX bonus)
<br />
AC: 36 Ancestral Guard
<br />

<br />
Spell Pros
<br />
- Slows!  75% magic based slow or 60% disease based (most will have access only to the 50% diseased based for an alt).  The premier reason for choosing this class as a support character for your mage.  Your shammy and even a well geared Mage can pesudo tank mobs and get spells off while being hit by a slowed mob.
<br />

<br />
- Dots - Shammys Dots are some of the most formidable in the game and can help kill mobs over medium length engagements.
<br />

<br />
- Debuffs - While mages and shammys overlap in terms of Malosinia line, shammys do have a larger advantage with Malos, 55 unresistable debuff which dwarfs our Mala.  They also have the Cripple line to help weaken a mobs offense and procs.
<br />

<br />
- Buffs - What more needs to be said.  Almost all stats save for Int/Wis can be buffed including resists in the order of 60+.  50% haste to cap off the pet cant be all that bad.  25hp regen!. 
<br />

<br />
- Canni / Regen - Very nice method to regen mana that can keep those slows and other spells coming. 
<br />

<br />
Spell Cons
<br />
- Very expensive fast heals and their cheal is less than 2k over 10 secs.  Fail to get slow on a very tough mob and you may not have time to recover.
<br />

<br />
Notes
<br />
- I almost always have mana for my shaman or can get it back pretty fast with Canni / Hots.  
<br />
- In conjunction with earth pet, can easily get mobs slowed safely so that if necessary the shammy can easily off tank one or root park one if needed.
<br />
- If mana is low and pet has plenty of health, you can turn down the speed of the kill via slow, SoR, Dots and med though the combat while using Canni/HoT to get your shammy back in good shape.<br />_________________<br />- I can tank dammit!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
