				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My 2box (2nd pc.. not eq windows)  is a druid.  Love having druid.  Porting is nice, Succor is nice.. Snare makes a huge difference.  I use air pet a lot, and since we cant snare/root and druid is great at both.  Im not complaining.   Regen, 3k heal, resists, a little spot nuking when I see the need.   Would slow be nice too?  sure it would.  But I wouldn't trade at this point.   Once druid gets DC for animals, there are a few places I won't mind hunting with the additional DPS.   
<br />

<br />
I have a necro, don't really play it.  Why?  Too much freakin work.  Mage rarely has to change keys.  Druid pet rarely does either once I get exp'ing.  Fast heal, C-heal, 1 nuke, 1 dot, regen, root, snare, evac.   All macro'd for easy use, with /assist main and /follow hotkeys used generously.  
<br />

<br />
And what's not to like about druid with succor/egress and mage with coh.  My guild loves going places with me, as.. depending on where we go, I can get people across zones much easier than trying to lead people in places they've never been.   And if someone shows up late (seb is a good example)  druid egress's, invites, coh both back.
<br />

<br />
Pet gets PotC or Pot9.. yeah.. its not virtue.  It doesnt suck either.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
