			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Micker wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I triple account on 1 box</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
How do you do that??  What progam you running and how do you switch fast enough to each screen??</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I use winXP which lets me alt-tab without a third party tool like eqwindows.  I also use a freeware memory defrager which helps things to run smoothly.  Also no window runs in over 1024x768 16bit and sound needs to be disabled on each window.  I read that you can have sound enabled on one instance but havent tried it yet.
<br />

<br />
Once everything is up and running command and control can be a bugger.  Optimally, I get each character to the camp seperately and camp them.  Only zone one character at a time - unless it's a retreat situation.
<br />

<br />
A typical fight for me goes as follows:
<br />
SK Pulls with a snare, runs back to camp.  Turn out auto-attack.  Alt-tab to chanter.
<br />

<br />
Chanter slows the SK's target and mezzes any adds.  Once the adds are mezzed he slows them.  Check SK HPS, if they looking good add a dot then switch to the SK.  Otherwise switch to the cleric and throw on a heal
<br />

<br />
Once back at the SK taunt and bash if the mob dies quick, switch to the mezzed mob (if any) and add a Siphon Str (for agro), taunt, then add snare dot (it'll be so much agro the mob will never go near the chanter).  If the fight is taking a while, switch to the chanter and refresh mezz.
<br />

<br />
Rinse and repeat.
<br />

<br />
The trick is I use macros for everything.  For example the chanter to slow is:
<br />
/assist SK
<br />
/stand
<br />
/cast 6 (slow)
<br />
/pause x (I think it's 25)
<br />
/sit
<br />

<br />
So I'm switched to the SK or the Cleric by the time the chanter is even finished casting.  You must do everything you can to reduce your human workload for this to work.  Mezzing is of course hugely labor intensive so I try not to pull any more than 3 mobs at a time.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
