<br />

<br />
What he said.  
<br />

<br />
Using a cleric means you keep your mage as a main. 
<br />

<br />
In an outdoor zone you can kill anything that doesn't kill your pet in 13 seconds are less.  That includes five of the Gallor{Sp} goloms in the Plane of Justice Caves.  With this combo, the trick is to keep the aggro on the pet.  As long as it stays on the pet, you will win unless it kills our pet in less time than a CH. 
<br />

<br />
I now have a 63rd level mage and 61st level cleric.  I can go to any pre-pop dungeon and crawl/explore it without any problems.  Also, with this combo, I can add just about any other character class and have a trio.  
<br />

<br />
I am condsidering getting a third account to level an enchanter.  However, the enchanter will have to be the main because the class that get's/handles aggro must be your main box.  When I go on raids I switch the cleric to the main box because if when the ##(*&$ hits the fan, the magic can only kill it faster and get killed him self while the cleric can root, heal, lead the mobs away and DI/DB, Group Heal, Stun, etc.<br />_________________<br />Dabrighter Blazemeister
