				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">For 2 boxing with a mage theres pretty much 3 main options to take into account... though pretty much already listed I'll go through the.. hi i just wokeup and read the post for the first time rundown <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Cleric:
<br />
- Heals
<br />
- Virtue
<br />
- Pacify
<br />
- Root
<br />
- Rez
<br />

<br />
Druid:
<br />
- Heals
<br />
- Pot9
<br />
- Nuke
<br />
- Ports
<br />
- Snare(kite)
<br />
- Root
<br />
- Can charm animals
<br />

<br />
Shammy:
<br />
- Heals
<br />
- Focus
<br />
- Slow
<br />
- Root
<br />
- Dot
<br />
- Added pet
<br />
- Nearly unlimited mana
<br />

<br />
The key to your first boxed char in my view is obviously heals. Where you go from there it depends on your play style. Do you want to straight up pet tank? What kind of HP buffs do you want? Do you want rez? Do you want slow? Do you want the ability to kite? Do you xp in out of the way places w/no books and want a porter?
<br />

<br />
Personally My choice would be the Shammy.. you get more for your buck from him (imo) with slow. However this is a personal choice and I know just as many arguments for cleric and druid bots. It all depends on your play style and what you want out of the boxed chars.. take into consideration the above "features," think about your play style, and thats the best way to go. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />Xeg-<a href="http://www.havenlight.com" target="_blank">Havenlight</a>
<br />
Arch Convoker-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=190198" target="_blank">Sage Civin Slayerofbunnies</a>  
<br />
Dread Lord-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=637778" target="_blank">Duke Zenlan Destroyerofbunnies</a> 
<br />
Archon-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=947084" target="_blank">Venerable Britnae Roasterofbunnies</a>
<br />
Coercer-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=964973" target="_blank">Master Seikmeht Devourerofbunnies</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
