				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">the_gnome:
<br />

<br />
Odd you have problems with aggro using a cleric.  There is absolutely zero aggro associated with healing & buffing any pet.  I can therefore assume you are doing one of two things:
<br />

<br />
1) buffing and/or healing your mage
<br />
2) casting on the mobs
<br />

<br />
To give you an example:  when I box in PoTactics my cleric is sitting where my pet is guarded to prevent out-of-range problems when I generate aggro or the mob starts running.  Though the cleric is very much KOS to the diaku, he can CH the pet + sit + CH + sit + CH + sit...all while being actively closer to the mob than my rooting earth pet.  He never takes a single hit.
<br />

<br />
This has held true in virtually every zone in every expansion in every type of environment on single pulls & trains.  As long as cleric does not in any way cast on a mob or a player or itself - it is immunity.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=501504">Anthe Battlecaster</a>
<br />
Uses
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=962390">Improved Healing V</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
