				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I play a 65 120aa enchanter as my main, and started a mage when I discovered how much fun they are. Levelled up with KEI and epic haste on pets from level 1 onwards. Currently 65, 20aa mage.
<br />

<br />
I play both chanter and mage together, on seperate PCs (eqw when i have to, but my PC isn't big enough to do it well), but chanter is usually the main character. Sometimes, when it's just a DC pet, and KEI and haste, the mage is a main, or rather they're both doing the same job (pet attack, nuke, maintain buffs).
<br />

<br />
Obviously I don't tend to play too much with just the two characters - no healing except for the pet makes it a very risky proposition. Charm or DC "solo" play is sometimes made much easier by the mage pet, but I tend to prefer the grouping, and it's an awesome combination for grouping!
<br />

<br />

<br />
The "Best" combination really depends on what you want to do, and whether you have regular playmates of any particular class.
<br />

<br />
Druid, shaman, cleric give good options for playing by yourself, staying alive and keeping the mage as your main character.
<br />

<br />
Enchanter, bard, necro, beastlord give further great possibilities for group play due to their versatility, but really only beastlord, manasong bard or buffbot enchanter allow you to keep your mage as the main focus of your attention. None of these are primary healers, so to play by yourself with them becomes quite tough - if you get aggro, you're either dead or very hurt.
<br />

<br />
Other classes don't seem to combine too well with magicians. Melee and hybrids are movement intensive for positioning, encouraging them to be the main character without giving you independence to play without others, wizard doesn't offer healing or versatility but could be great if you wanted to be major raid DPS.<br />_________________<br />Kantia Subtilis - Coercer
<br />
Kantoo - Arch Convoker
<br />
Innoruuk Server</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
