			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I box a shaman and don't regret it.  I could easily box my 65 cleric with my mage, but the fact is Mage+pet+Shaman+pet > Mage+pet+cleric unless you need pacify.  I don't think I have come across a mob that the mage pet could tank unslowed with a cleric healing that the mage pet couldn't tank slowed with a shaman healing + dotting + nuking + pet.
<br />

<br />
I suppose you could mention unslowable mobs, but all things considered, the shaman offers more the the duo than a cleric.  Mobs die faster and easier due to the contribution the shaman brings, whereas the cleric is simply there for heals, buffs, minor DPS and pacify if needed.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
