				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>bandoslav Grumsonavitch wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">the_gnome:
<br />

<br />
Odd you have problems with aggro using a cleric.  There is absolutely zero aggro associated with healing & buffing any pet.  I can therefore assume you are doing one of two things:
<br />

<br />
1) buffing and/or healing your mage
<br />
2) casting on the mobs
<br />

<br />
To give you an example:  when I box in PoTactics my cleric is sitting where my pet is guarded to prevent out-of-range problems when I generate aggro or the mob starts running.  Though the cleric is very much KOS to the diaku, he can CH the pet + sit + CH + sit + CH + sit...all while being actively closer to the mob than my rooting earth pet.  He never takes a single hit.
<br />

<br />
This has held true in virtually every zone in every expansion in every type of environment on single pulls & trains.  As long as cleric does not in any way cast on a mob or a player or itself - it is immunity.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
And if not KOS and you blow the heal and pet dies.   And mage dies before a heal goes off.  The mob/mobs wander away and you can rez in place.  Only works if cleric is not KoS to the mob.  
<br />

<br />
Healing or buffing the pet gets zero aggro to the cleric.  If you have the mana and the mobs and pre-pop, it is a very effective way to break a room.<br />_________________<br />Dabrighter Blazemeister
